<Base title="Terms of Service" description="Basic terms for using PerlCode.">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 prose dark:prose-invert">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p>
      By using PerlCode, you agree that the content is provided “as-is” with no warranty.
      Code examples are intended for learning and may require adaptation for your environment.
    </p>
    <h2>Sandbox execution</h2>
    <p>
      Some pages include a “Run” button. Execution is performed in a restricted sandbox with
      limits (time/memory/network). Do not rely on it for sensitive workloads.
    </p>
    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Do not attempt to abuse the sandbox or disrupt the service.</li>
      <li>Do not scrape at high volume without permission.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Base>

